  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  At least 12 years of age

          -  Single ventricle congenital heart disease

          -  Require cardiac magnetic resonance imaging (MRI) for clinical purposes.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  &lt; 12 years of age

          -  Pregnancy or women who may become pregnant (sexually active and unwilling to use birth
             control)

          -  Patients taking cyclosporin or glyburide

          -  Patients with baseline liver dysfunction (aspartate aminotransferase or alanine
             aminotransferase &gt; 3 times upper limit of normal)

          -  Contraindications to MRI (including pacemakers)

          -  Use of Bosentan within one month prior to enrollment
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
